\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Poggles\
\
A Peggle-inspired game built for Steam using the Godot engine.\
\
## Core Gameplay\
\
- **Cannon** at the top of the screen \'97 aim and shoot a ball\
- Ball bounces off **pegs** with physics-based movement\
- **Peg types:**\
  - Orange \'97 must clear all to win the level\
  - Blue \'97 normal scoring pegs\
  - Green \'97 triggers a power-up\
  - Purple \'97 bonus points\
- **Sliding bucket** at the bottom \'97 catching the ball earns a free ball\
- Limited number of balls per level\
- Clear all orange pegs to win\
\
## Tech Stack\
\
- **Engine:** Godot 4.x (free, open-source, excellent 2D physics)\
- **Language:** GDScript or C# (TBD)\
- **Steam Integration:** GodotSteam plugin\
- **Platform:** Windows (Steam)\
\
## Godot MCP Servers\
\
For AI-assisted development with Claude, set up one of these on the dev PC:\
\
| Option | Repo | Strength |\
|---|---|---|\
| **GDAI MCP** (recommended) | `3ddelano/gdai-mcp-plugin-godot` | Most features, auto-screenshots, full scene/node control |\
| **Coding-Solo** | `Coding-Solo/godot-mcp` | Most popular (~2.1k stars), simple setup, run/debug focus |\
| **slangwald** | `slangwald/godot-mcp` | Runtime scene editing, input simulation, Python-based |\
